A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 County Boards of Education – Appointed Members in Leadership Positions –
3 Prohibition
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting certain appointed members of a county board of education
5 from serving in certain leadership positions on the county board; requiring the State
6 Department of Education to send a certain notice to a county board if the county
7 board violates a certain prohibition; specifying certain penalties that may be imposed
8 on county boards and appointed members for the continued violation of a certain
9 prohibition; and generally relating to leadership positions on county boards of
10 education.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Education
13 Section 3–106
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Education
19 3–106.
20 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
21 INDICATED.
22 (2) (I) “APPOINTED MEMBER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL SERVING ON
23 A COUNTY BOARD WHO IS APPOINTED TO THE POSITION BY A GOVERNMENT
24 OFFICIAL OR GOVERNMENTAL BODY.
